  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Final Word in His Son"
      title: "God\u2019s Final Word in His Son"
      number: 1
      content: '  God, having spoken to the fathers long ago in [the voices and writings
        of] the prophets in many separate revelations [each of which set forth a
        portion of the truth], and in many ways, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'has in these last days spoken [with finality] to us in [the person
        of One who is by His character and nature] His Son [namely Jesus], whom He
        appointed heir and lawful owner of all things, through whom also He created
        the universe [that is, the universe as a space-time-matter continuum]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The Son is the radiance and only expression of the glory of [our
        awesome] God [reflecting God\u2019s Shekinah glory, the Light-being, the
        brilliant light of the divine], and the exact representation and perfect
        imprint of His [Father\u2019s] essence, and upholding and maintaining and
        propelling all things [the entire physical and spiritual universe] by His
        powerful word [carrying the universe along to its predetermined goal]. When
        He [Himself and no other] had [by offering Himself on the cross as a sacrifice
        for sin] accomplished purification from sins and established our freedom
        from guilt, He sat down [revealing His completed work] at the right hand
        of the Majesty on high [revealing His Divine authority], "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "having become as much superior to angels, since He has inherited
        a more excellent and glorious name than they [that is, Son\u2014the name
        above all names].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For to which of the angels did the Father ever say,\u201CYou are
        My Son,Today I have begotten (fathered) You [established You as a Son, with
        kingly dignity]\u201D?And again [did He ever say to the angels],\u201CI shall
        be a Father to HimAnd He shall be a Son to Me\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "  And when He again brings the firstborn [highest-ranking Son] into
        the world, He says,\u201CAnd all the angels of God are to worship Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And concerning the angels He says,\u201CWho makes His angels winds,And
        His ministering servants flames of fire [to do His bidding].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But about the Son [the Father says to Him],\u201CYour throne, O God,
        is forever and ever,And the  scepter of [absolute] righteousness is the scepter
        of  His kingdom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You have loved righteousness [integrity, virtue, uprightness in purpose]
        and have hated lawlessness [injustice, sin].Therefore God, Your God, Has
        anointed YouWith the oil of gladness above Your companions.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And,\u201CYou, Lord, laid the foundation of the earth in the beginning,And
        the heavens are the works of Your hands;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They will perish, but You remain [forever and ever];And they will
        all wear out like a garment,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And like a robe You will roll them up;Like a garment they will be
        changed.But  You are the same [forever],And Your years will never end.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But to which of the angels has the Father ever said,\u201CSit at
        My right hand [together with me in royal dignity],Until I make your enemiesA
        footstool for your feet [in triumphant conquest]\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Are not all the angels ministering spirits sent out [by God] to serve
        (accompany, protect) those who will inherit salvation? [Of course they are!]
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Give Heed'
      title: Give Heed
      number: 1
      content: "    For this reason [that is, because of God\u2019s final revelation
        in His Son Jesus and because of Jesus\u2019 superiority to the angels] we
        must pay much closer attention than ever to the things that we have heard,
        so that we do not [in any way] drift away from truth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if the message given through angels [the Law given to Moses]
        was authentic and unalterable, and every violation and disobedient act received
        an appropriate penalty, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'how will we escape [the penalty] if we ignore such a great salvation
        [the gospel, the new covenant]? For it was spoken at first by the Lord, and
        it was confirmed to us and proved authentic by those who personally heard
        [Him speak], '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Earth Subject to Man'
      title: Earth Subject to Man
      number: 4
      content: '[and besides this evidence] God also testifying with them [confirming
        the message of salvation], both by signs and wonders and by various miracles
        [carried out by Jesus and the apostles] and by [granting to believers the]
        gifts of the Holy Spirit according to His own will.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It was not to angels that God subjected the [inhabited] world of
        the future [when Christ reigns], about which we are speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But one has [solemnly] testified somewhere [in Scripture], saying,\u201CWhat
        is man, that You are mindful of him,Or the son of man, that You graciously
        care for him?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You have made him for a little while lower [in status] than the angels;You
        have crowned him with glory and honor,  And set him over the works of Your
        hands;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Jesus Briefly Humbled'
      title: Jesus Briefly Humbled
      number: 8
      content: "You have put all things in subjection under his feet [confirming
        his supremacy].\u201DNow in putting all things in subjection to man, He left
        nothing outside his control. But at present we do not yet see all things
        subjected to him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But we do see Jesus, who was made lower than the angels for a little
        while [by taking on the limitations of humanity], crowned with glory and
        honor because of His suffering of death, so that by the grace of God [extended
        to sinners] He might experience death for [the sins of] everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For it was fitting for God [that is, an act worthy of His divine
        nature] that He, for whose sake are all things, and through whom are all
        things, in bringing many sons to glory, should make the author and founder
        of their salvation perfect through suffering [bringing to maturity the human
        experience necessary for Him to be perfectly equipped for His office as High
        Priest]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Both Jesus who sanctifies and those who are sanctified [that is,
        spiritually transformed, made holy, and set apart for God\u2019s purpose]
        are all from one Father; for this reason He is not ashamed to call them brothers
        and sisters, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "saying,\u201CI will declare Your (the Father\u2019s) name to My brethren
        (believers),In the midst of the congregation I will sing Your praise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And again [He says],\u201CMy trust  and  confident hope will be placed
        in Him.\u201DAnd again,\u201CHere I am, I and the children whom God has given
        Me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore, since [these His] children share in flesh and blood [the
        physical nature of mankind], He Himself in a similar manner also shared in
        the same [physical nature, but without sin], so that through [experiencing]
        death He might make powerless (ineffective, impotent) him who had the power
        of death\u2014that is, the devil\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and [that He] might free all those who through [the haunting] fear
        of death were held in slavery throughout their lives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For, as we all know, He (Christ) does not take hold of [the fallen]
        angels [to give them a helping hand], but He does take hold of [the fallen]
        descendants of Abraham [extending to them His hand of deliverance]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore, it was essential that He had to be made like His brothers
        (mankind) in every respect, so that He might [by experience] become a merciful
        and faithful High Priest in things related to God, to make atonement (propitiation)
        for the people\u2019s sins [thereby wiping away the sin, satisfying divine
        justice, and providing a way of reconciliation between God and mankind]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Because He Himself [in His humanity] has suffered in being tempted,
        He is able to help and provide immediate assistance to those who are being
        tempted and exposed to suffering.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus Our High Priest'
      title: Jesus Our High Priest
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore, holy brothers and sisters, who share in the heavenly
        calling, [thoughtfully and attentively] consider the Apostle and High Priest
        whom we confessed [as ours when we accepted Him as Savior], namely, Jesus; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He was faithful to Him who appointed Him [Apostle and High Priest],
        as Moses also was faithful in all God\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Yet Jesus has been considered worthy of much greater glory and honor
        than Moses, just as the builder of a house has more honor than the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For every house is built by someone, but the builder of all things
        is God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now Moses was faithful in [the administration of] all God\u2019s
        house, [but only] as a ministering servant, [his ministry serving] as a testimony
        of the things which were to be spoken afterward [the revelation to come in
        Christ]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "but Christ is faithful as a Son over His [Father\u2019s] house. And
        we are His house if we hold fast our confidence and sense of triumph in our
        hope [in Christ].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore, just as the Holy Spirit says,\u201CToday if you hear His
        voice,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Do not harden your hearts as [your fathers did] in the rebellion
        [of Israel at Meribah],On the day of testing in the wilderness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Where your fathers tried Me by testing [My forbearance and tolerance],And
        saw My works for forty years[And found I stood their test].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Therefore I was angered with this generation,And I said, \u2018They
        always go astray in their heart,And they did not know My ways [nor become
        progressively better and more intimately acquainted with them]\u2019;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: The Peril of Unbelief'
      title: The Peril of Unbelief
      number: 11
      content: "So I swore [an oath] in My wrath,\u2018They shall not enter My rest
        [the promised land].\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Take care, brothers and sisters, that there not be in any one of
        you a wicked, unbelieving heart [which refuses to trust and rely on the Lord,
        a heart] that turns away from the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But continually encourage one another every day, as long as it is
        called \u201CToday\u201D [and there is an opportunity], so that none of you
        will be hardened [into settled rebellion] by the deceitfulness of sin [its
        cleverness, delusive glamour, and sophistication]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For we [believers] have become partakers of Christ [sharing in all
        that the Messiah has for us], if only we hold firm our newborn confidence
        [which originally led us to Him] until the end, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "while it is said,\u201CToday [while there is still opportunity] if
        you hear His voice,Do not harden your heart, as when they provoked Me [in
        the rebellion in the desert at Meribah].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For who were they who heard and yet provoked Him [with rebellious
        acts]? Was it not all those who came out of Egypt led by Moses? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And with whom was He angry for forty years? Was it not with those
        who sinned, whose dead bodies were scattered in the desert? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And to whom did He swear [an oath] that they would not enter His
        rest, but to those who disobeyed [those who would not listen to His word]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So we see that they were not able to enter [into His rest\u2014the
        promised land] because of unbelief and an unwillingness to trust in God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Believer\u2019s Rest"
      title: "The Believer\u2019s Rest"
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore, while the promise of entering His rest still remains
        and is freely offered today, let us fear, in case any one of you may seem
        to come short of reaching it or think he has come too late. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For indeed we have had the good news [of salvation] preached to us,
        just as the Israelites also [when the good news of the promised land came
        to them]; but the message they heard did not benefit them, because it was
        not united with faith [in God] by those who heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For we who believe [that is, we who personally trust and confidently
        rely on God] enter that rest [so we have His inner peace now because we are
        confident in our salvation, and assured of His power], just as He has said,\u201CAs
        I swore [an oath] in My wrath,They shall not enter My rest,\u201D[this He
        said] although His works were completed from the foundation of the world
        [waiting for all who would believe].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For somewhere [in Scripture] He has said this about the seventh day:
        \u201CAnd God rested on the seventh day from all His works\u201D; "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and again in this, \u201CThey shall not enter My rest.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore, since the promise remains for some to enter His rest,
        and those who formerly had the good news preached to them failed to [grasp
        it and did not] enter because of [their unbelief evidenced by] disobedience, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He again sets a definite day, [a new] \u201CToday,\u201D [providing
        another opportunity to enter that rest by] saying through David after so
        long a time, just as has been said before [in the words already quoted],\u201CToday
        if you hear His voice,Do not harden your hearts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '[This mention of a rest was not a reference to their entering into
        Canaan.] For if Joshua had given them rest, God would not speak about another
        day [of opportunity] after that. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So there remains a [full and complete] Sabbath rest for the people
        of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the one who has once entered His rest has also rested from [the
        weariness and pain of] his [human] labors, just as God rested from [those
        labors uniquely] His own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let us therefore make every effort to enter that rest [of God, to
        know and experience it for ourselves], so that no one will fall by following
        the same example of disobedience [as those who died in the wilderness]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the word of God is living and active and full of power [making
        it operative, energizing, and effective]. It is sharper than any two-edged
        sword, penetrating as far as the division of the soul and spirit [the completeness
        of a person], and of both joints and marrow [the deepest parts of our nature],
        exposing and judging the very thoughts and intentions of the heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And not a creature exists that is concealed from His sight, but all
        things are open and exposed, and revealed to the eyes of Him with whom we
        have to give account.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Inasmuch then as we [believers] have a great High Priest who has
        [already ascended and] passed through the heavens, Jesus the Son of God,
        let us hold fast our confession [of faith and cling tenaciously to our absolute
        trust in Him as Savior]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For we do not have a High Priest who is unable to sympathize and
        understand our weaknesses and temptations, but One who has been tempted [knowing
        exactly how it feels to be human] in every respect as we are, yet without
        [committing any] sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore let us [with privilege] approach the throne of grace [that
        is, the throne of God\u2019s gracious favor] with confidence and without
        fear, so that we may receive mercy [for our failures] and find [His amazing]
        grace to help in time of need [an appropriate blessing, coming just at the
        right moment]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Perfect High Priest'
      title: The Perfect High Priest
      number: 1
      content: '  For every high priest chosen from among men is appointed [to act]
        on behalf of men in things relating to God, so that he may offer both gifts
        and sacrifices for sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He is able to deal gently with the spiritually ignorant and misguided,
        since he is also subject to human weakness; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and because of this [human weakness] he is required to offer sacrifices
        for sins, for himself as well as for the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And besides, one does not appropriate for himself the honor [of being
        high priest], but he who is called by God, just as Aaron was.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So too Christ did not glorify Himself so as to be made a high priest,
        but He [was exalted and appointed by the One] who said to Him,\u201CYou are
        My Son,Today I have begotten (fathered) You [declared Your authority and
        rule over the nations]\u201D;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "just as He also says in another place,\u201CYou are a priest [appointed]
        foreverAccording to the order of  Melchizedek.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "In the days of His earthly life, Jesus offered up both [specific]
        petitions and [urgent] supplications [for that which He needed] with fervent
        crying and tears to the One who was [always] able to save Him from death,
        and He was heard because of His reverent submission toward God [His sinlessness
        and His unfailing determination to do the Father\u2019s will]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Although He was a Son [who had never been disobedient to the Father],
        He learned [active, special] obedience through what He suffered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And having been made perfect [uniquely equipped and prepared as Savior
        and retaining His integrity amid opposition], He became the source of eternal
        salvation [an eternal inheritance] to all those who obey Him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'being designated by God as High Priest according to the order of
        Melchizedek.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Concerning this we have much to say, and it is hard to explain, since
        you have become dull and sluggish in [your spiritual] hearing and disinclined
        to listen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For though by this time you ought to be teachers [because of the
        time you have had to learn these truths], you actually need someone to teach
        you again the elementary principles of God\u2019s word [from the beginning],
        and you have come to be continually in need of milk, not solid food. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For everyone who lives on milk is [doctrinally inexperienced and]
        unskilled in the word of righteousness, since he is a spiritual infant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: But solid food is for the [spiritually] mature, whose senses are trained
        by practice to distinguish between what is morally good and what is evil.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Peril of Falling Away'
      title: The Peril of Falling Away
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore let us get past the elementary stage in the teachings
        about the Christ, advancing on to maturity and perfection and spiritual completeness,
        [doing this] without laying again a foundation of repentance from dead works
        and of faith toward God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'of teaching about washings (ritual purifications), the laying on
        of hands, the resurrection of the dead, and eternal judgment. [These are
        all important matters in which you should have been proficient long ago.] '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And we will do this [that is, proceed to maturity], if God permits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For [it is impossible to restore to repentance] those who have once
        been enlightened [spiritually] and who have tasted and consciously experienced
        the heavenly gift and have shared in the Holy Spirit, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and have tasted and consciously experienced the good word of God
        and the powers of the age (world) to come, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and then have fallen away\u2014it is impossible to bring them back
        again to repentance, since they again nail the Son of God on the cross [for
        as far as they are concerned, they are treating the death of Christ as if
        they were not saved by it], and are holding Him up again to public disgrace. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For soil that drinks the rain which often falls on it and produces
        crops useful to those for whose benefit it is cultivated, receives a blessing
        from God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Better Things for You'
      title: Better Things for You
      number: 8
      content: 'but if it persistently produces thorns and thistles, it is worthless
        and close to being cursed, and it ends up being burned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But, beloved, even though we speak to you in this way, we are convinced
        of better things concerning you, and of things that accompany salvation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For God is not unjust so as to forget your work and the love which
        you have shown for His name in ministering to [the needs of] the saints (God\u2019s
        people), as you do. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And we desire for each one of you to show the same diligence [all
        the way through] so as to realize and enjoy the full assurance of hope until
        the end, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'so that you will not be [spiritually] sluggish, but [will instead
        be] imitators of those who through faith [lean on God with absolute trust
        and confidence in Him and in His power] and by patient endurance [even when
        suffering] are [now] inheriting the promises.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For when God made the promise to Abraham, He swore [an oath] by Himself,
        since He had no one greater by whom to swear, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "saying, \u201CI will surely bless you and I will surely multiply
        you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And so, having patiently waited, he realized the promise [in the
        miraculous birth of Isaac, as a pledge of what was to come from God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Indeed men swear [an oath] by one greater than themselves, and with
        them [in all disputes] the oath serves as confirmation [of what has been
        said] and is an end of the dispute. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the same way God, in His desire to show to the heirs of the promise
        the unchangeable nature of His purpose, intervened and guaranteed it with
        an oath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'so that by two unchangeable things [His promise and His oath] in
        which it is impossible for God to lie, we who have fled [to Him] for refuge
        would have strong encouragement and indwelling strength to hold tightly to
        the hope set before us. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "This hope [this confident assurance] we have as an anchor of the
        soul [it cannot slip and it cannot break down under whatever pressure bears
        upon it]\u2014a safe and steadfast hope that enters within the veil [of the
        heavenly temple, that most Holy Place in which the very presence of God dwells], "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: where Jesus has entered [in advance] as a forerunner for us, having
        become a High Priest forever according to the order of Melchizedek.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Melchizedek\u2019s Priesthood Like Christ\u2019s"
      title: "Melchizedek\u2019s Priesthood Like Christ\u2019s"
      number: 1
      content: '  For this Melchizedek, king of Salem, priest of the Most High God,
        met Abraham as he returned from the slaughter of the kings and blessed him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and Abraham gave him a tenth of all [the spoil]. He is, first of
        all, by the translation of his name, king of righteousness, and then he is
        also king of Salem, which means king of peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Without [any record of] father or mother, nor ancestral line, without
        [any record of] beginning of days (birth) nor ending of life (death), but
        having been made like the Son of God, he remains a priest without interruption
        and without successor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now pause and consider how great this man was to whom Abraham, the
        patriarch, gave a tenth of the spoils. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "It is true that those descendants of Levi who are charged with the
        priestly office are commanded in the Law to collect tithes from the people\u2014which
        means, from their kinsmen\u2014though these have descended from Abraham. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But this person [Melchizedek] who is not from their Levitical ancestry
        received tithes from Abraham and blessed him who possessed the promises [of
        God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Yet it is beyond all dispute that the lesser person is always blessed
        by the greater one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Furthermore, here [in the Levitical priesthood] tithes are received
        by men who are subject to death; but in that case [concerning Melchizedek],
        they are received by one of whom it is testified that he lives on [perpetually]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'A person might even say that Levi [the father of the priestly tribe]
        himself, who received tithes, paid tithes through Abraham [the father of
        all Israel and of all who believe], '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'for Levi was still in the loins (unborn) of his forefather [Abraham]
        when Melchizedek met him (Abraham).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now if perfection [a perfect fellowship between God and the worshiper]
        had been attained through the Levitical priesthood (for under it the people
        were given the Law) what further need was there for another and different
        kind of priest to arise, one in the manner of Melchizedek, rather than one
        appointed to the order of Aaron? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For when there is a change in the priesthood, there is of necessity
        a change of the law [concerning the priesthood] as well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the One of whom these things are said belonged [not to the priestly
        line of Levi but] to another tribe, from which no one has officiated or served
        at the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For it is evident that our Lord descended from [the tribe of] Judah,
        and Moses mentioned nothing about priests in connection with that tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And this becomes even more evident if another priest arises in the
        likeness of Melchizedek, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'who has become a priest, not on the basis of a physical and legal
        requirement in the Law [concerning his ancestry as a descendant of Levi],
        but on the basis of the power of an indestructible and endless life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For it is attested [by God] of Him,\u201CYou (Christ) are a Priest
        foreverAccording to the order of Melchizedek.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For, on the one hand, a former commandment is cancelled because of
        its weakness and uselessness [because of its inability to justify the sinner
        before God] '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '(for the Law never made anything perfect); while on the other hand
        a better hope is introduced through which we now continually draw near to
        God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And indeed it was not without the taking of an oath [that Christ
        was made priest] '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "(for those Levites who formerly became priests [received their office]
        without [its being confirmed by the taking of] an oath, but this One [was
        designated] with an oath through the One who said to Him,\u201CThe Lord has
        swornAnd will not change His mind  or  regret it,\u2018You (Christ) are a
        Priest forever\u2019\u2009\u201D).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And so [because of the oath\u2019s greater strength and force] Jesus
        has become the certain guarantee of a better covenant [a more excellent and
        more advantageous agreement; one that will never be replaced or annulled].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The [former successive line of] priests, on the one hand, existed
        in greater numbers because they were each prevented by death from continuing
        [perpetually in office]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'but, on the other hand, Jesus holds His priesthood permanently and
        without change, because He lives on forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Therefore He is able also to save forever (completely, perfectly,
        for eternity) those who come to God through Him, since He always lives to
        intercede and intervene on their behalf [with God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'It was fitting for us to have such a High Priest [perfectly adapted
        to our needs], holy, blameless, unstained [by sin], separated from sinners
        and exalted higher than the heavens; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'who has no day by day need, like those high priests, to offer sacrifices,
        first of all for his own [personal] sins and then for those of the people,
        because He [met all the requirements and] did this once for all when He offered
        up Himself [as a willing sacrifice]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: For the Law appoints men as high priests who are weak [frail, sinful,
        dying men], but the word of the oath [of God], which came after [the institution
        of] the Law, permanently appoints [as priest] a Son who has been made perfect
        forever.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Better Ministry'
      title: A Better Ministry
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the main point of what we have to say is this: we have such
        a High Priest, [the Christ] who is seated [in the place of honor] at the
        right hand of the throne of the Majesty (God) in heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'a Minister (Officiating Priest) in the holy places and in the true
        tabernacle, which is erected not by man, but by the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For every high priest is appointed to offer both gifts and sacrifices;
        so it is essential for this One also to have something to offer. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now if He were [still living] on earth, He would not be a priest
        at all, for there are priests who offer the gifts [to God] in accordance
        with the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They serve as a pattern and foreshadowing of [what has its true existence
        and reality in] the heavenly things (sanctuary). For when Moses was about
        to erect the tabernacle, he was warned by God, saying, \u201CSee that you
        make it all [exactly] according to the pattern which was shown to you on
        the mountain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: A New Covenant'
      title: A New Covenant
      number: 6
      content: 'But as it is, Christ has acquired a [priestly] ministry which is
        more excellent [than the old Levitical priestly ministry], for He is the
        Mediator (Arbiter) of a better covenant [uniting God and man], which has
        been enacted and rests on better promises.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For if that first covenant had been faultless, there would have been
        no occasion for a second one or an attempt to institute another one [the
        new covenant]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "However, God finds fault with them [showing its inadequacy] when
        He says,\u201CBehold, the days will come, says the Lord,When I will make 
        and  ratify a new covenantWith the house of Israel and with the house of
        Judah;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Not like the covenant that I made with their fathersOn the day when
        I took them by the handTo lead them out of the land of Egypt;For they did
        not abide in My covenant,And so I withdrew My favor  and  disregarded them,
        says the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For this is the covenant that I will make with the house of IsraelAfter
        those days, says the Lord:I will imprint My laws upon their minds [even upon
        their innermost thoughts and understanding],And engrave them upon their hearts
        [effecting their regeneration].And I will be their God,And they shall be
        My people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And it will not be [necessary] for each one to teach his fellow citizen,Or
        each one his brother, saying, \u2018Know [by experience, have knowledge of]
        the Lord,\u2019For all will know [Me by experience and have knowledge of]
        Me,From the least to the greatest of them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For I will be merciful  and  gracious toward their wickedness,And
        I will remember their sins no more.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When God speaks of \u201CA new covenant,\u201D He makes the first
        one obsolete. And whatever is becoming obsolete (out of use, annulled) and
        growing old is ready to disappear."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Old and the New'
      title: The Old and the New
      number: 1
      content: '  Now even the first covenant had regulations for divine worship
        and for the earthly sanctuary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A tabernacle (sacred tent) was put up, the outer one or first section,
        in which were the lampstand and the table with [its loaves of] the sacred
        showbread; this is called the Holy Place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Behind the second veil there was another tabernacle [the inner one
        or second section] known as the Holy of Holies, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'having the golden altar of incense and the ark of the covenant covered
        entirely with gold. This contained a golden jar which held the manna, and
        the rod of Aaron that sprouted, and the [two stone] tablets of the covenant
        [inscribed with the Ten Commandments]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and above the ark were the [golden] cherubim of glory overshadowing
        the mercy seat; but we cannot now go into detail about these things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now when these things have been prepared in this way, the priests
        continually enter the outer [or first section of the] tabernacle [that is,
        the Holy Place] performing [their ritual acts of] the divine worship, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but into the second [inner tabernacle, the Holy of Holies], only
        the high priest enters [and then only] once a year, and never without [bringing
        a sacrifice of] blood, which he offers [as a substitutionary atonement] for
        himself and for the sins of the people committed in ignorance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'By this the Holy Spirit signifies that the way into the Holy Place
        [the true Holy of Holies and the presence of God] has not yet been disclosed
        as long as the first or outer tabernacle is still standing [that is, as long
        as the Levitical system of worship remains a recognized institution], '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'for this [first or outer tabernacle] is a symbol [that is, an archetype
        or paradigm] for the present time. Accordingly both gifts and sacrifices
        are offered which are incapable of perfecting the conscience and renewing
        the [inner self of the] worshiper. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For they [the gifts, sacrifices, and ceremonies] deal only with [clean
        and unclean] food and drink and various ritual washings, [mere] external
        regulations for the body imposed [to help the worshipers] until the time
        of reformation [that is, the time of the new order when Christ will establish
        the reality of what these things foreshadow\u2014a better covenant].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But when Christ appeared as a High Priest of the good things to come
        [that is, true spiritual worship], He entered through the greater and more
        perfect tabernacle, not made with hands, that is to say, not a part of this
        [material] creation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He went once for all into the Holy Place [the Holy of Holies of heaven,
        into the presence of God], and not through the blood of goats and calves,
        but through His own blood, having obtained and secured eternal redemption
        [that is, the salvation of all who personally believe in Him as Savior]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For if the sprinkling of [ceremonially] defiled persons with the
        blood of goats and bulls and the ashes of a [burnt] heifer is sufficient
        for the cleansing of the body, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'how much more will the blood of Christ, who through the eternal [Holy]
        Spirit willingly offered Himself unblemished [that is, without moral or spiritual
        imperfection as a sacrifice] to God, cleanse your conscience from dead works
        and lifeless observances to serve the ever living God?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For this reason He is the Mediator and Negotiator of a new covenant
        [that is, an entirely new agreement uniting God and man], so that those who
        have been called [by God] may receive [the fulfillment of] the promised eternal
        inheritance, since a death has taken place [as the payment] which redeems
        them from the sins committed under the obsolete first covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For where there is a will and  testament involved, the death of the
        one who made it must be established, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for a will and testament takes effect [only] at death, since it is
        never in force as long as the one who made it is alive. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'So even the first covenant was not put in force without [the shedding
        of] blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For when every commandment in the Law had been read by Moses to all
        the people, he took the blood of the calves and goats [which had been sacrificed],
        together with water and scarlet wool and with a bunch of hyssop, and he sprinkled
        both the scroll itself and all the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "saying, \u201CThis is the blood of the covenant [that seals and ratifies
        the agreement] which God ordained  and  commanded [me to deliver to] you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And in the same way he sprinkled both the tabernacle and all the
        containers and sacred utensils of worship with the blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'In fact under the Law almost everything is cleansed with blood, and
        without the shedding of blood there is no forgiveness [neither release from
        sin and its guilt, nor cancellation of the merited punishment].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Therefore it was necessary for the [earthly] copies of the heavenly
        things to be cleansed with these, but the heavenly things themselves required
        far better sacrifices than these. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For Christ did not enter into a holy place made with hands, a mere
        copy of the true one, but [He entered] into heaven itself, now to appear
        in the very presence of God on our behalf; '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'nor did He [enter into the heavenly sanctuary to] offer Himself again
        and again, as the high priest enters the Holy Place every year with blood
        that is not his own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Otherwise, He would have needed to suffer over and over since the
        foundation of the world; but now once for all at the consummation of the
        ages He has appeared and been publicly manifested to put away sin by the
        sacrifice of Himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And just as it is appointed and destined for all men to die once
        and after this [comes certain] judgment, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: so Christ, having been offered once and once for all to bear [as a
        burden] the sins of many, will appear a second time [when he returns to earth],
        not to deal with sin, but to bring salvation to those who are eagerly and
        confidently waiting for Him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: One Sacrifice of Christ Is Sufficient'
      title: One Sacrifice of Christ Is Sufficient
      number: 1
      content: "  For since the Law has only a shadow [just a pale representation]
        of the good things to come\u2014not the very image of those things\u2014it
        can never, by offering the same sacrifices continually year after year, make
        perfect those who approach [its altars]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if it were otherwise, would not these sacrifices have stopped
        being offered? For the worshipers, having once [for all time] been cleansed,
        would no longer have a consciousness of sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But [as it is] these [continual] sacrifices bring a fresh reminder
        of sins [to be atoned for] year after year, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'for it is impossible for the blood of bulls and goats to take away
        sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Therefore, when Christ enters into the world, He says,\u201CSacrifice
        and offering You have not desired,But [instead] You have prepared a body
        for Me [to offer];  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In burnt offerings and  sacrifices  for sin You have taken no delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then I said, \u2018Behold, I have comeTo do Your will, O God\u2014[To
        fulfill] what is written of Me in the scroll of the book.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "After saying [in the citation] above, \u201CYou have neither desired,
        nor have You taken delight in sacrifices and offerings and whole burnt offerings
        and  sacrifices  for sin\u201D (which are offered according to the Law) "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "then He said, \u201CBehold, I have come to do Your will.\u201D [And
        so] He does away with the first [covenant as a means of atoning for sin based
        on animal sacrifices] so that He may inaugurate and establish the second
        [covenant by means of obedience]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And in accordance with this will [of God] we [who believe in the
        message of salvation] have been sanctified [that is, set apart as holy for
        God and His purposes] through the offering of the body of Jesus Christ (the
        Messiah, the Anointed) once for all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Every priest stands [at his altar of service] ministering daily,
        offering the same sacrifices over and over, which are never able to strip
        away sins [that envelop and cover us]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'whereas Christ, having offered the one sacrifice [the all-sufficient
        sacrifice of Himself] for sins for all time, sat down [signifying the completion
        of atonement for sin] at the right hand of God [the position of honor], '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'waiting from that time onward until his enemies are made a footstool
        for His feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For by the one offering He has perfected forever and completely cleansed
        those who are being sanctified [bringing each believer to spiritual completion
        and maturity]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Holy Spirit also adds His testimony to us [in confirmation
        of this]; for after having said,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThis is the covenant that I will make with themAfter those
        days, says the Lord:I will imprint My laws upon their heart,And on their
        mind I will inscribe them [producing an inward change],\u201D  He then says,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CAnd their sins and their lawless actsI will remember no more
        [no longer holding their sins against them].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: A New and Living Way'
      title: A New and Living Way
      number: 18
      content: 'Now where there is [absolute] forgiveness and complete cancellation
        of the penalty of these things, there is no longer any offering [to be made
        to atone] for sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Therefore, believers, since we have confidence and full freedom to
        enter the Holy Place [the place where God dwells] by [means of] the blood
        of Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'by this new and living way which He initiated and opened for us through
        the veil [as in the Holy of Holies], that is, through His flesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'and since we have a great and wonderful Priest [Who rules] over the
        house of God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'let us approach [God] with a true and sincere heart in unqualified
        assurance of faith, having had our hearts sprinkled clean from an evil conscience
        and our bodies washed with pure water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Let us seize and hold tightly the confession of our hope without
        wavering, for He who promised is reliable and trustworthy and faithful [to
        His word]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and let us consider [thoughtfully] how we may encourage one another
        to love and to do good deeds, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Christ or Judgment'
      title: Christ or Judgment
      number: 25
      content: "not forsaking our meeting together [as believers for worship and
        instruction], as is the habit of some, but encouraging one another; and all
        the more [faithfully] as you see the day [of Christ\u2019s return] approaching.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For if we go on willfully and deliberately sinning after receiving
        the knowledge of the truth, there no longer remains a sacrifice [to atone]
        for our sins [that is, no further offering to anticipate], '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'but a kind of awful and terrifying expectation of [divine] judgment
        and the fury of a fire  and  burning wrath which will consume the adversaries
        [those who put themselves in opposition to God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Anyone who has ignored and set aside the Law of Moses is put to death
        without mercy on the testimony of two or three witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'How much greater punishment do you think he will deserve who has
        rejected and trampled under foot the Son of God, and has considered unclean
        and common the blood of the covenant that sanctified him, and has insulted
        the Spirit of grace [who imparts the unmerited favor and blessing of God]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "For we know Him who said, \u201CVengeance is Mine [retribution and
        the deliverance of justice rest with Me], I will repay [the wrongdoer].\u201D
        And again, \u201CThe Lord will judge His people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'It is a fearful and terrifying thing to fall into the hands of the
        living God [incurring His judgment and wrath].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'But remember the earlier days, when, after being [spiritually] enlightened,
        you [patiently] endured a great conflict of sufferings, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'sometimes by being made a spectacle, publicly exposed to insults
        and distress, and sometimes by becoming companions with those who were so
        treated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For you showed sympathy and deep concern for those who were imprisoned,
        and you joyfully accepted the [unjust] seizure of your belongings and the
        confiscation of your property, conscious of the fact that you have a better
        possession and a lasting one [prepared for you in heaven]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Do not, therefore, fling away your [fearless] confidence, for it
        has a glorious and great reward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'For you have need of patient endurance [to bear up under difficult
        circumstances without compromising], so that when you have carried out the
        will of God, you may receive and enjoy to the full what is promised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'For yet in a very little while,He who is coming will come, and will
        not delay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "But My righteous one [the one justified by faith] shall live by faith
        [respecting man\u2019s relationship to God and trusting Him];And if he draws
        back [shrinking in fear], My soul has no delight in him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: But our way is not that of those who shrink back to destruction, but
        [we are] of those who believe [relying on God through faith in Jesus Christ,
        the Messiah] and by this confident faith preserve the soul.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Triumphs of Faith'
      title: The Triumphs of Faith
      number: 1
      content: "  Now faith is the assurance (title deed, confirmation) of things
        hoped for (divinely guaranteed), and the evidence of things not seen [the
        conviction of their reality\u2014faith comprehends as fact what cannot be
        experienced by the physical senses]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For by this [kind of] faith the men of old gained [divine] approval.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'By faith [that is, with an inherent trust and enduring confidence
        in the power, wisdom and goodness of God] we understand that the worlds (universe,
        ages) were framed and created [formed, put in order, and equipped for their
        intended purpose] by the word of God, so that what is seen was not made out
        of things which are visible. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'By faith Abel offered to God a more acceptable sacrifice than Cain,
        through which it was testified of him that he was righteous (upright, in
        right standing with God), and God testified by accepting his gifts. And though
        he died, yet through [this act of] faith he still speaks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'By faith [that pleased God] Enoch was caught up and taken to heaven
        so that he would not have a glimpse of death; and he was not found because
        God had taken him; for even before he was taken [to heaven], he received
        the testimony [still on record] that he had walked with God and pleased Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But without faith it is impossible to [walk with God and] please
        Him, for whoever comes [near] to God must [necessarily] believe that God
        exists and that He rewards those who [earnestly and diligently] seek Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'By faith [with confidence in God and His word] Noah, being warned
        by God about events not yet seen, in reverence prepared an ark for the salvation
        of his family. By this [act of obedience] he condemned the world and became
        an heir of the righteousness which comes by faith.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'By faith Abraham, when he was called [by God], obeyed by going to
        a place which he was to receive as an inheritance; and he went, not knowing
        where he was going. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'By faith he lived as a foreigner in the promised land, as in a strange
        land, living in tents [as nomads] with Isaac and Jacob, who were fellow heirs
        of the same promise. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For he was [waiting expectantly and confidently] looking forward
        to the city which has foundations, [an eternal, heavenly city] whose architect
        and builder is God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'By faith even Sarah herself received the ability to conceive [a child],
        even [when she was long] past the normal age for it, because she considered
        Him who had given her the promise to be reliable and true [to His word]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So from one man, though he was [physically] as good as dead, were
        born as many descendants  as the stars of heaven in number, and innumerable
        as the sand on the seashore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "All these died in faith [guided and sustained by it], without receiving
        the [tangible fulfillment of God\u2019s] promises, only having seen (anticipated)
        them and having welcomed them from a distance, and having acknowledged that
        they were strangers and exiles on the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now those who say such things make it clear that they are looking
        for a country of their own. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And if they had been thinking of that country from which they departed
        [as their true home], they would have had [a continuing] opportunity to return. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But the truth is that they were longing for a better country, that
        is, a heavenly one. For that reason God is not ashamed [of them or] to be
        called their God [even to be surnamed their God\u2014the God of Abraham,
        Isaac, and Jacob]; for He has prepared a city for them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'By faith Abraham, when he was tested [that is, as the testing of
        his faith was still in progress], offered up Isaac, and he who had received
        the promises [of God] was ready to sacrifice his only son [of promise]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "to whom it was said, \u201CThrough Isaac your descendants shall be
        called.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For he considered [it reasonable to believe] that God was able to
        raise Isaac even from among the dead. [Indeed, in the sense that he was prepared
        to sacrifice Isaac in obedience to God] Abraham did receive him back [from
        the dead] figuratively speaking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'By faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau [believing what God revealed
        to him], even regarding things to come. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'By faith Jacob, as he was dying, blessed each of the sons of Joseph,
        and bowed in worship, leaning on the top of his staff. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'By faith Joseph, when he was dying, referred to [the promise of God
        for] the exodus of the sons of Israel [from Egypt], and gave instructions
        concerning [the burial of] his bones [in the land of the promise].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "By faith Moses, after his birth, was hidden for three months by his
        parents, because they saw he was a beautiful and divinely favored child;
        and they were not afraid of the king\u2019s (Pharaoh\u2019s) decree. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "By faith Moses, when he had grown up, refused to be called the son
        of Pharaoh\u2019s daughter, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'because he preferred to endure the hardship of the people of God
        rather than to enjoy the passing pleasures of sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He considered the reproach of the Christ [that is, the rebuke he
        would suffer for his faithful obedience to God] to be greater wealth than
        all the treasures of Egypt; for he looked ahead to the reward [promised by
        God]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'By faith he left Egypt, being unafraid of the wrath of the king;
        for he endured [steadfastly], as seeing Him who is unseen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'By faith he kept the Passover and the sprinkling of the blood [on
        the doorposts], so that the destroyer of the firstborn would not touch them
        (the firstborn of Israel). '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'By faith the people [of Israel] crossed the Red Sea as though they
        were passing through dry land; but when the Egyptians attempted it they were
        drowned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'By faith the walls of Jericho fell down after they had been encircled
        for seven days [by Joshua and the sons of Israel]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'By faith Rahab the prostitute was not destroyed along with those
        who were disobedient, because she had welcomed the spies [sent by the sons
        of Israel] in peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And what more shall I say? For time will fail me if I tell of Gideon,
        Barak, Samson, Jephthah, of David and Samuel and the prophets, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'who by faith [that is, with an enduring trust in God and His promises]
        subdued kingdoms, administered justice, obtained promised blessings, closed
        the mouths of lions, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'extinguished the power of [raging] fire, escaped the edge of the
        sword, out of weakness were made strong, became mighty and unbeatable in
        battle, putting enemy forces to flight. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Women received back their dead by resurrection; and others were tortured
        [to death], refusing to accept release [offered on the condition of denying
        their faith], so that they would be resurrected to a better life; '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and others experienced the trial of mocking and scourging [amid torture],
        and even chains and imprisonment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'They were stoned [to death], they were sawn in two, they were lured
        with tempting offers [to renounce their faith], they were put to death by
        the sword; they went about wrapped in the skins of sheep and goats, utterly
        destitute, oppressed, cruelly treated '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: '(people of whom the world was not worthy), wandering in deserts and
        mountains and [living in] caves and holes in the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And all of these, though they gained [divine] approval through their
        faith, did not receive [the fulfillment of] what was promised, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: because God had us in mind and had something better for us, so that
        they [these men and women of authentic faith] would not be made perfect [that
        is, completed in Him] apart from us.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jesus, the Example'
      title: Jesus, the Example
      number: 1
      content: "  Therefore, since we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses
        [who by faith have testified to the truth of God\u2019s absolute faithfulness],
        stripping off every unnecessary weight and the sin which so easily and cleverly
        entangles us, let us run with endurance and active persistence the race that
        is set before us, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '[looking away from all that will distract us and] focusing our eyes
        on Jesus, who is the Author and Perfecter of faith [the first incentive for
        our belief and the One who brings our faith to maturity], who for the joy
        [of accomplishing the goal] set before Him endured the cross, disregarding
        the shame, and sat down at the right hand of the throne of God [revealing
        His deity, His authority, and the completion of His work].  '
      comments: []
    - name: "3: A Father\u2019s Discipline"
      title: "A Father\u2019s Discipline"
      number: 3
      content: 'Just consider and meditate on Him who endured from sinners such bitter
        hostility against Himself [consider it all in comparison with your trials],
        so that you will not grow weary and lose heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'You have not yet struggled to the point of shedding blood in your
        striving against sin; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and you have forgotten the divine word of encouragement which is
        addressed to you as sons,\u201CMy son, do not make light of the discipline
        of the Lord,And do not lose heart  and  give up when you are corrected by
        Him;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord disciplines  and  corrects those whom He loves,And He
        punishes every son whom He receives  and  welcomes [to His heart].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'You must submit to [correction for the purpose of] discipline; God
        is dealing with you as with sons; for what son is there whom his father does
        not discipline? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Now if you are exempt from correction and without discipline, in
        which all [of God\u2019s children] share, then you are illegitimate children
        and not sons [at all]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Moreover, we have had earthly fathers who disciplined us, and we
        submitted and respected them [for training us]; shall we not much more willingly
        submit to the Father of spirits, and live [by learning from His discipline]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For our earthly fathers disciplined us for only a short time as seemed
        best to them; but He disciplines us for our good, so that we may share His
        holiness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the time being no discipline brings joy, but seems sad and painful;
        yet to those who have been trained by it, afterwards it yields the peaceful
        fruit of righteousness [right standing with God and a lifestyle and attitude
        that seeks conformity to God\u2019s will and purpose].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So then, strengthen hands that are weak and knees that tremble. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Cut through and make smooth, straight paths for your feet [that are
        safe and go in the right direction], so that the leg which is lame may not
        be put out of joint, but rather may be healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Continually pursue peace with everyone, and the sanctification
        without which no one will [ever] see the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "See to it that no one falls short of God\u2019s grace; that no root
        of resentment springs up and causes trouble, and by it many be defiled; "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and [see to it] that no one is immoral or godless like Esau, who
        sold his own birthright for a single meal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Contrast of Sinai and Zion'
      title: Contrast of Sinai and Zion
      number: 17
      content: 'For you know that later on, when he wanted [to regain title to] his
        inheritance of the blessing, he was rejected, for he found no opportunity
        for repentance [there was no way to repair what he had done, no chance to
        recall the choice he had made], even though he sought for it with [bitter]
        tears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For you have not come [as did the Israelites in the wilderness] to
        a mountain that can be touched and to a blazing fire, and to gloom and darkness
        and a raging windstorm, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and to the blast of a trumpet and a sound of words [such that] those
        who heard it begged that nothing more be said to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For they could not bear the command, \u201CIf even a wild animal
        touches the mountain, it will be stoned [to death].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "In fact, so terrifying was the sight, that Moses said, \u201CI am
        filled with fear and trembling.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But you have come to Mount Zion and to the city of the living God,
        the heavenly Jerusalem, and to myriads of angels [in festive gathering], '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and to the general assembly and assembly of the firstborn who are
        registered [as citizens] in heaven, and to God, who is Judge of all, and
        to the spirits of the righteous (the redeemed in heaven) who have been made
        perfect [bringing them to their final glory], '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: The Unshaken Kingdom'
      title: The Unshaken Kingdom
      number: 24
      content: 'and to Jesus, the Mediator of a new covenant [uniting God and man],
        and to the sprinkled blood, which speaks [of mercy], a better and nobler
        and more gracious message than the blood of Abel [which cried out for vengeance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "See to it that you do not refuse [to listen to] Him who is speaking
        [to you now]. For if those [sons of Israel] did not escape when they refused
        [to listen to] him who warned them on earth [revealing God\u2019s will],
        how much less will we escape if we turn our backs on Him who warns from heaven? "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "His voice shook the earth [at Mount Sinai] then, but now He has given
        a promise, saying, \u201CYet once more I will shake not only the earth, but
        also the [starry] heaven.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Now this [expression], \u201CYet once more,\u201D indicates the removal
        and final transformation of all those things which can be shaken\u2014that
        is, of that which has been created\u2014so that those things which cannot
        be shaken may remain. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Therefore, since we receive a kingdom which cannot be shaken, let
        us show gratitude, and offer to God pleasing service and acceptable worship
        with reverence and awe; '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: for our God is [indeed] a consuming fire.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Changeless Christ'
      title: The Changeless Christ
      number: 1
      content: '  Let love of your fellow believers continue. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Do not neglect to extend hospitality to strangers [especially among
        the family of believers\u2014being friendly, cordial, and gracious, sharing
        the comforts of your home and doing your part generously], for by this some
        have entertained angels without knowing it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Remember those who are in prison, as if you were their fellow prisoner,
        and those who are mistreated, since you also are in the body [and subject
        to physical suffering]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Marriage is to be held in honor among all [that is, regarded as something
        of great value], and the marriage bed undefiled [by immorality or by any
        sexual sin]; for God will judge the sexually immoral and adulterous. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Let your character [your moral essence, your inner nature] be free
        from the love of money [shun greed\u2014be financially ethical], being content
        with what you have; for He has said, \u201CI will never [under any circumstances]
        desert you [nor give you up nor leave you without support, nor will I in
        any degree leave you helpless], nor will I forsake  or  let you down  or 
        relax My hold on you [assuredly not]!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So we take comfort and are encouraged and confidently say,\u201CThe
        Lord is my Helper [in time of need], I will not be afraid.What will man do
        to me?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Remember your leaders [for it was they] who brought you the word
        of God; and consider the result of their conduct [the outcome of their godly
        lives], and imitate their faith [their conviction that God exists and is
        the Creator and Ruler of all things, the Provider of eternal salvation through
        Christ, and imitate their reliance on God with absolute trust and confidence
        in His power, wisdom, and goodness]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Jesus Christ is [eternally changeless, always] the same yesterday
        and today and forever. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not be carried away by diverse and strange teachings; for it is
        good for the heart to be established and strengthened by grace and not by
        foods [rules of diet and ritualistic meals], which bring no benefit or spiritual
        growth to those who observe them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We have an altar from which those who serve the tabernacle (sacred
        tent) have no right to eat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For the bodies of those animals whose blood is brought into the sanctuary
        by the high priest as an offering for sin, are burned outside the camp. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore Jesus also suffered and died outside the [city] gate so
        that He might sanctify and set apart for God as holy the people [who believe]
        through [the shedding of] His own blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So, let us go out to Him outside the camp, bearing His contempt [the
        disgrace and shame that He had to suffer]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: God-pleasing Sacrifices'
      title: God-pleasing Sacrifices
      number: 14
      content: 'For here we have no lasting city, but we are seeking the city which
        is to come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Through Him, therefore, let us at all times offer up to God a sacrifice
        of praise, which is the fruit of lips that thankfully acknowledge and confess
        and glorify His name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Do not neglect to do good, to contribute [to the needy of the church
        as an expression of fellowship], for such sacrifices are always pleasing
        to God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Obey your [spiritual] leaders and submit to them [recognizing their
        authority over you], for they are keeping watch over your souls and continually
        guarding your spiritual welfare as those who will give an account [of their
        stewardship of you]. Let them do this with joy and not with grief and groans,
        for this would be of no benefit to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Keep praying for us, for we are convinced that we have a good conscience,
        seeking to conduct ourselves honorably [that is, with moral courage and personal
        integrity] in all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Benediction'
      title: Benediction
      number: 19
      content: 'And I urge all of you to pray earnestly, so that I may be restored
        to you soon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now may the God of peace [the source of serenity and spiritual well-being]
        who brought up from the dead our Lord Jesus, the great Shepherd of the sheep,
        through the blood that sealed and ratified the eternal covenant, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'equip you with every good thing to carry out His will and strengthen
        you [making you complete and perfect as you ought to be], accomplishing in
        us that which is pleasing in His sight, through Jesus Christ, to whom be
        the glory forever and ever. Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'I call on you, brothers and sisters, listen [patiently] to this message
        of exhortation and encouragement, for I have written to you briefly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Notice that our brother Timothy has been released [from prison].
        If he comes soon, I will see you [along with him]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Give our greetings to all of your [spiritual] leaders and to all
        of the saints (God\u2019s people). Those [Christians] from Italy send you
        their greetings.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Grace be with you all.
      comments: []
